<br>
Most people are very courteous when I tell them that I can't be of any assistance to them.  However, there are some people who have made it necessary to keep my identity hidden.  Example?  This happened yesterday.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Guy:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  can u summon my corpse plz?<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Me:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Sorry, but I don't have the spell yet.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Guy:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  umm ok  why dont u have it u get the spell at 39 ...  u suck ur probly lying bcuz u dont want to hlp me<br>
<br>
Yadda, yadda, yadda.  I forgot to mention this character was a SK.  I nearly blew up at him, telling him, &quot;Well, if Verant hadn't been a bunch of idiots and not given you SKs the spell, maybe I'd have a better chance of having it!&quot;<br>
<br>
...which brings me to another thing.  Yes, I know I chose the necro class knowing that I'm not very effective in groups.  Verant tried to counter this statement, saying that we necros can do a lot in groups (more specifically, high level raids)!  We can summon corpses!  Well, okay, that was all good and well, seeing as how we were the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> only</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> class at the time with such an ability, so at least a few necros were guaranteed on raids.  But no, let's give SK's the spell... hm.  Who needs necros now?  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :/ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":/"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Heh... just my little rant.<br>
<br>
